</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Manhattan Beach" /><category term="Golden Hour" /><category term="Lifeguard Towers" /><category term="Boats" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Lifeguard tower and dories, this evening on The Strand at Marine Ave.]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2025/2501_A7R00698.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2025/2501_A7R00698.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Low Tide Sunset</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/250114/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Low Tide Sunset" /><published>2025-01-14T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2025-01-14T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/low-tide</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/250114/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
    Ripples in the water under the Hermosa Beach Pier at low tide.
</p>

<p class="jp">
<span class="title_jp">干潮時の夕日</span>

ハーモサビーチの桟橋の下、干潮時の浜辺に広がる波紋。
</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Hermosa Beach" /><category term="Sunset" /><category term="Hermosa Pier" /><category term="Low Tide" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Ripples in the water under the Hermosa Beach Pier at low tide.]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2025/2501_A7R00650-HDR.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2025/2501_A7R00650-HDR.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Pier Reflection</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/250113/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Pier Reflection" /><published>2025-01-13T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2025-01-13T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/pier-reflection</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/250113/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
The setting sun shines through the Hermosa Beach Pier, which is reflected on the beach at low tide.
</p>

<p class="jp">
<span class="title_jp">桟橋の反射</span>

夕日がハーモサビーチの桟橋を通して輝き、その反射光が干潮時にビーチに映し出されます。
</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Hermosa Beach" /><category term="Sunset" /><category term="Hermosa Pier" /><category term="Low Tide" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[The setting sun shines through the Hermosa Beach Pier, which is reflected on the beach at low tide.]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2025/2501_A7R00609.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2025/2501_A7R00609.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Pt. Vicente Lighthouse</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/250111/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Pt. Vicente Lighthouse" /><published>2025-01-11T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2025-01-11T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/lighthouse</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/250111/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
Once a month, the 100 year old <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Point_Vicente_Lighthouse" target="_blank">Point Vicente Lighthouse</a> grounds are opened and visitors can walk around the lighthouse area. Still can't go in the lighthouse, unfortunately.
</p>

<p class="jp">
<span class="title_jp">ポイント・ビセンテ灯台</span>

100年の歴史を持つポイント・ビセンテ灯台の敷地は、月に一度一般公開され、来訪者は灯台の周辺を散策することができます。残念ながら、灯台の中に入ることはできません。

</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Palos Verdes" /><category term="Lighthouses" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Once a month, the 100 year old Point Vicente Lighthouse grounds are opened and visitors can walk around the lighthouse area. Still can't go in the lighthouse, unfortunately.]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2025/2501_A7R00536_ai.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2025/2501_A7R00536_ai.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Fire Red Sunset</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/250108/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Fire Red Sunset" /><published>2025-01-08T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2025-01-08T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/vicente-bluffs</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/250108/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
    Smoke from the Los Angeles wildfires causing a red sunset tonight. Looking through reeds at the Vicente Bluffs in Rancho Palos Verdes.
</p>

<p class="jp">
<span class="title_jp">ファイヤーレッドの夕焼け</span>

ロサンゼルス山火事による煙が、今夜の夕焼けを赤く染めている。ランチョ・パロス・ベルデスのビセンテ断崖を葦越しに見る。

</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Palos Verdes" /><category term="Sunset" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Smoke from the Los Angeles wildfires causing a red sunset tonight. Looking through reeds at the Vicente Bluffs in Rancho Palos Verdes.]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2025/2501_A7R00502-3.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2025/2501_A7R00502-3.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry></feed>